David Kirkpatrick, who coauthored

00:03:00.547 --> 00:03:01.381
that piece, has covered

00:03:01.381 --> 00:03:02.682
the region extensively.

00:03:02.682 --> 00:03:03.516
He joins us now.

00:03:03.516 --> 00:03:04.651
David, the article you wrote

00:03:04.651 --> 00:03:06.753
is is fascinating.

00:03:06.753 --> 00:03:11.558
What what were they thinking?

00:03:11.624 --> 00:03:12.659
You know,

00:03:12.659 --> 00:03:16.062
the picture that emerged was desperation.

00:03:16.129 --> 00:03:16.863
I should tell you

00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:19.599
that when my colleague Adam

00:03:19.599 --> 00:03:21.301
Rasgon and I,

00:03:21.301 --> 00:03:22.168
both Rasgon

00:03:22.168 --> 00:03:24.804
and I spoke to Mousa Abu Marzouk,

00:03:24.804 --> 00:03:26.105
he was at pains to say, no,

00:03:26.105 --> 00:03:28.208
we have not despaired, we're strong.

00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:29.442
But the takeaway was

00:03:29.442 --> 00:03:31.744
that they basically feel like their backs

00:03:31.744 --> 00:03:33.479
against are against the wall.

00:03:33.479 --> 00:03:35.648
It was a, you know, a familiar

00:03:35.648 --> 00:03:36.749
litany of grievances

00:03:36.749 --> 00:03:37.750
about the occupation,

00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:39.152
about Israeli settlements

00:03:39.152 --> 00:03:40.053
in the West Bank,

00:03:40.053 --> 00:03:41.054
about the management

00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:42.121
of the Al-Aqsa mosque,

00:03:42.121 --> 00:03:44.257
which is very important to Palestinians

00:03:44.257 --> 00:03:46.025
and Muslims everywhere.

00:03:46.025 --> 00:03:46.960
But added to

00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:48.828
that was an increased sense

00:03:48.828 --> 00:03:49.295
of desperation

00:03:49.295 --> 00:03:51.030
because of the right wing government

00:03:51.030 --> 00:03:52.465
around Netanyahu,

00:03:52.465 --> 00:03:53.733
because of the messages

00:03:53.733 --> 00:03:54.567
that it's conveying

00:03:54.567 --> 00:03:56.102
about its lack of receptivity

00:03:56.102 --> 00:03:57.503
to any kind of

00:03:57.503 --> 00:03:58.771
Palestinian political entity

00:03:58.771 --> 00:04:00.740
alongside side Israel.

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.642
And also a sense of betrayal

00:04:02.642 --> 00:04:05.044
as the other Arab states

00:04:05.044 --> 00:04:06.512
more and more accommodate

00:04:06.512 --> 00:04:07.780
themselves to Israel,

00:04:07.780 --> 00:04:09.182
you know, begin to recognize

00:04:09.182 --> 00:04:10.783
Israel and Saudi Arabia,

00:04:10.783 --> 00:04:11.951
the most important of those.

00:04:11.951 --> 00:04:13.753
The latest in line

00:04:13.753 --> 00:04:15.355
to make an agreement like that.

00:04:15.355 --> 00:04:16.522
So it's really a time

00:04:16.522 --> 00:04:19.092
when I think from his point of view,

00:04:19.192 --> 00:04:22.562
little choice.

00:04:22.629 --> 00:04:26.466
So for for Hamas, it would be a success.

00:04:26.466 --> 00:04:27.900
If you can talk about the murder

00:04:27.900 --> 00:04:29.102
of so many civilians

00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:30.136
as a success

00:04:30.136 --> 00:04:31.471
in their in their calculus,

00:04:31.471 --> 00:04:33.473
as if that Saudi deal

00:04:33.473 --> 00:04:34.307
does not go through.

00:04:34.307 --> 00:04:36.809
Saudi Arabia does not recognize

00:04:36.809 --> 00:04:38.544
the state of Israel.

00:04:38.544 --> 00:04:40.280
And also,

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:41.581
they have these hostages

00:04:41.581 --> 00:04:44.117
who they have wanted to trade in the past

00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:47.820
and I assume want to trade now.

00:04:47.887 --> 00:04:49.222
Yeah, that's all true.

00:04:49.222 --> 00:04:49.522
You know,

00:04:49.522 --> 00:04:50.490
and we pressed him

00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:51.991
on the sort of intelligible

00:04:51.991 --> 00:04:53.059
strategic reasons.

00:04:53.059 --> 00:04:53.293
You know,

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:54.994
did you do this because of Saudi Arabia?

00:04:54.994 --> 00:04:56.996
Did you do this for prisoner exchanges?

00:04:56.996 --> 00:04:58.298
And there wasn't a clear answer

00:04:58.298 --> 00:04:59.265
because he was very frank

00:04:59.265 --> 00:05:00.633
that he didn't think they could dissuade

00:05:00.633 --> 00:05:01.301
Saudi Arabia.

00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:02.302
Saudi Arabia is going to do

00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:04.237
what Saudi Arabia is going to do.

00:05:04.237 --> 00:05:04.871
And yeah,

00:05:04.871 --> 00:05:06.039
I'm sure they'll want to exchange

00:05:06.039 --> 00:05:07.006
these prisoners.

00:05:07.006 --> 00:05:08.508
But at the same time,

00:05:08.508 --> 00:05:09.275
they this

00:05:09.275 --> 00:05:12.011
this attack has brought an enormous,

00:05:12.011 --> 00:05:14.947
enormous degree of pain on the Gaza

00:05:14.947 --> 00:05:16.115
and part of the Palestinians

00:05:16.115 --> 00:05:17.850
living in Gaza.

00:05:17.850 --> 00:05:19.052
And when we pressed him

00:05:19.052 --> 00:05:21.321
about how the strategic advantages,

00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:22.522
the practical strategic

00:05:22.522 --> 00:05:23.823
advantage of this attack

00:05:23.823 --> 00:05:25.892
could justify that sacrifice,

00:05:25.892 --> 00:05:27.894
his answers were very abstract,

00:05:27.894 --> 00:05:28.661
very nebulous.

00:05:28.661 --> 00:05:29.829
He was really looking towards

00:05:29.829 --> 00:05:31.698
a very, very distant horizon.

00:05:31.698 --> 00:05:34.267
All he could say was, you know, for years

00:05:34.267 --> 00:05:35.902
they've been fighting on our territory

00:05:35.902 --> 00:05:36.969
and killing us.

00:05:36.969 --> 00:05:37.603
This time

00:05:37.603 --> 00:05:38.805
we're fighting on their territory

00:05:38.805 --> 00:05:41.374
for the first time, which is a

00:05:41.441 --> 00:05:42.608
you know, it's a symbolic

00:05:42.608 --> 00:05:47.113
victory of sorts, but it's not much.

00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:47.847
We should point out

00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:49.215
and you point this out in

00:05:49.215 --> 00:05:50.450
in the article in The New Yorker,

00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:52.051
which I encourage people to read.

00:05:52.051 --> 00:05:52.985
He lied to you.

